summary:
Over 30 years of experience in all planning aspects related to airport projects throughout the world, both greenfield and brownfield. As airport architect/ planner responsible for feasibility studies, master plan studies, terminal development studies from concept design to the final stage of construction, as well as all of the other airport ancillary facilities. 

- Terminal area master planning and development studies;
- Concept design, preliminary design, final design and tender documents for terminal buildings, and all
  other ancillary buildings, including ATC towers, R & FFF, cargo facilities and MRO's; 
- Review on operational, commercial and technical aspects and recommendations for improvements of
  terminal facilities.

profile_positions.description:
SCAI, designers and consultants for the airport industry. We offering our broad expertise and experience as independent consultants for airport development, including airport master planning and feasibility studies, passenger terminal development and design, airport civil and pavement design and all other airport related facilities.

References: 
For many years the consultants of SCAI have succesfully provided expertise and innovative solutions for airport development projects throughout the world. In order to give you an overview of the capabilities and experiences of SCAI, we have listed a number of our most recent projects and assignments.

- Amsterdam Airport Schiphol: Asset management;
- Cambodia Airports, Phnom Penh and Siem Reap: Landside signage project;
- Bintan Airport Indonesia: Aerospace Park Long Term Vision;
- Ho Airport, Ghana: New domestic airport;
- Amsterdam Airport Schiphol: Maintenance strategy airside Infrastructure;
- Helsinki Airport: Master Plan second opinion study;
- Mauritius Airport: ATC Tower proposal;
- Bintan Airport Indonesia: New passenger terminal building;
- Nairobi Airport, Kenya: Proposal concept design interim passenger terminal;
- Krasnodar Airport, Russia, Master Plan;
- Regional Airports Indonesia: Master Plan and airport facilities development;
- Aberdeen Airport: Master Plan second opinion study;
- Amsterdam Airport Schiphol: Comprehensive study about passenger terminal principles.

Major assignments:

Stationed in Nairobi, Kenya, as lead architect responsible for:
- Review and recommendations for improvements of the planned expansion and refurbishing of the terminal building at Jomo Kenyatta International Airport.

Stationed in The Hague, Naco office, as lead architect responsible for:
- Concept design and preliminary design for a freight terminal at New Delhi Indira Gandhi International Airport, India;
- Terminal area master plan and concept design for the new terminal building of Vladivostok International Airport, Russian Federation; 
- Feasibility study, concept design and preliminary design for the new passenger terminal building of Da Nang International Airport, Vietnam;
- Modification plan for the passenger terminal building of Shanghai Pudong International Airport, China; 
- Feasibility study for the expansion and refurbishment of the E-finger at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol;
- The renovation and expansion of the KLM crew centre at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol.

Stationed at Frankfurt International Airport, Germany. As lead architect responsible for:
- Development potential for the new terminal 3; 
- Feasibility study and concept design for the refurbishment departure hall-B and B-finger;  
- Adjustment of terminal building 2 in view of handling the A380;
- Adjustment and development of the CD-finger in view of handling the A380;
- Development potential of the C-finger and the BC-area;
- Analysis and preliminary design of the integration of the A0-finger and the extended Lounge A.

Stationed in Muscat, Oman. As lead architect responsible for:
- Concept designs and final designs for the buildings components of the first development stage of the Al Musanah Airbase.

Stationed in Manila, the Philippines. As lead architect responsible for:
- Terminal area master plans, concept designs, preliminary designs, final designs and tender documents for the buildings components of the Third Airports Develpment Project.

Major assignments:

Stationed in The Hague, Naco office, as airport architect responsible for:
- Final design and preparation of tender documents for the the expansion programme for the King Abdulaziz International Airport in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia;
- Conceptual design for the extension of the terminal building of Münster Osnabrück Airport, Germany. The study also included the adaption of the building to future passenger traffic;
- Preliminary and final design and the preparation of tender documents for the rehabilitation and renovation of the terminal building at Sarajevo Airport, Bosnia Herzegovina;
- Preliminary design for a maintenance facility at Zagreb Airport, Croatia;
- Preliminary and final design, and the preparation of tender documents for a new cargo building at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol; 
- Architect of the new G-finger, with extensive passenger handling facilities for wide body aircraft. Also the preparation of the tender documents and supervision of the construction.

Stationed  in Jakarta, Indonesia. As architect responsible for:
 - Concept designs, preliminary designs, final designs and tender documents of the building facilities at Pattimura Airport, Ambon, Indonesia.

Stationed in Saudi Arabia as site architect responsible for:
- Supervision of construction of the new airport facilities at Al Ahsa Airport (Hofuf);
- Supervision of of construction of the new airport facilities at Al Baha Airport;
-Tender evaluations of various airports related to the Wide Body Aircraft Upgrading Programme and finalization of the World Islamic Conference Project at Taif Airport.
